gov.niarl.his.privacyca

Class TpmKeyParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.niarl.his.privacyca.TpmKeyParams

  • public class TpmKeyParams
extends Object

    This class is for the TCG's TPM_KEY_PARMS structure. Several other TCG values are defined here, as it seems appropriate to do so at the time.

    Author:
    schawki

      • setTrouSerSmode

        public void setTrouSerSmode(boolean state)
        Manually set TrouSerS mode. True means that the symmetric IV will appear at the beginning of a symmetrically encrypted blob, while false means that it will appear within a SymmetricKeyParams structure. This value is used when determining the format of the byte arrays that are passed back from the Privacy CA. By default the Privacy CA will set this value based on the format of the incoming identity request.
        Parameters:
        state -

      • getTrouSerSmode

        public boolean getTrouSerSmode()

        The current state of TrouSerS mode for this key params structure.
